<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-13776] [MongoDB] autoclosable cursor</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-13776</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/camel/blob/master/components/camel-mongodb3/src/main/java/org/apache/camel/component/mongodb3/MongoDbTailingThread.java#L86&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;following statement&lt;/a&gt; is not allowing the consumer to properly resume a previously stored tailing tracking.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;

&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;try&lt;/span&gt; (MongoCursor&amp;lt;Document&amp;gt; iterator = dbCol.find(gt(tailTracking.getIncreasingFieldName(), lastVal))

&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As the iterator is consumer outside that block, it is always impossible to recover any stopped tracking. The consumer test were infact previously @ignore-d for this reason.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Already working to fix this problem.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
